In my experience it is the indriyas that benefit first from the spiritual practice. However it is a stepping stone for one who endures the distraction and persists in the sadhana.

While doing Shiva and Kalabhairava homa i did pradakshina 3 - 5 times and always felt myself ascending a spirutual ladder with every round. Recently i tried Chandi Homa on a new moon night and i stammered, dozed off, stood up every 20 mins and yet in the morning i was feeling so light headed that i just can't wait to do it again.

IMHO the relation with god should be that of pure love, then there will be no room for fear. One act of humility and you can feel the embrace of god :)

Om Gan Ganapathaye Namah :)
